4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, if a minor is cited for a
6 tobacco violation, the citing agency must notify the
7 minor's parent or legal guardian.
8 This bill would authorize the Alabama State Law
9 Enforcement Agency (ALEA) to create an electronic
10 notification system under which a minor's parent or
11 legal guardian may be notified whenever a minor is
12 cited for a traffic infraction.
13 This bill would also give ALEA the authority to
14 adopt rules, restrictions, and eligibility requirements
15 that are necessary to create and manage the electronic
16 notification system.
17
18
19 A BILL
20 TO BE ENTITLED
21 AN ACT
22
23 Relating to traffic infractions; to authorize the
24 Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency to create an electronic
25 notification system by which parents and legal guardians shall
26 be notified when a minor receives certain traffic infractions;
27 and to grant the Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency certain
28 rulemaking authority.
Page 1

rulemaking authority.
HB318 INTRODUCED
29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
30 Section 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as
31 TJ's Law.
32 Section 2. (a) The Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency
33 (ALEA) shall develop and implement an electronic notification
34 system by which parents and legal guardians of minors shall
35 receive notification by reliable electronic means when the
36 minor under their legal custody is cited for any traffic
37 infraction.
38 (b) The Secretary of ALEA shall adopt rules,
39 restrictions, and eligibility requirements that are necessary
40 to implement the provisions of this section. At a minimum, the
41 rules shall include the following provisions:
42 (1) A parent or legal guardian may enroll in the
43 electronic notification system by providing sufficient
44 evidence that the minor is under his or her legal custody.
45 (2) A parent or legal guardian's access to the
46 electronic notification system for a minor under the parent or
47 guardian's legal custody automatically ends once the minor has
48 reached his or her 19th birthday.
49 (3) A minor may unenroll a parent or legal guardian
50 from the electronic notification system upon the submission of
51 clear evidence that the minor meets one of the following
52 requirements:
53 a. The minor is emancipated.
54 b. The minor is not dependent on a parent or legal
55 guardian for support and is living apart from his or her
56 parents or other individual in loco parentis.
Page 2

parents or other individual in loco parentis.
HB318 INTRODUCED
57 c. The minor is married.
58 d. The minor having been married is divorced.
59 e. The minor has borne a child.
60 (c) The creation and continuation of the electronic
61 notification system established in this section shall be
62 contingent upon the availability of funds.
63 (d) For the purposes of this section, the term "minor"
64 means an individual under the age of 19.
65 Section 3. This act shall become effective on October
66 1, 2026.
